Onboarding
Description: The "Onboarding" custom object in Salesforce is designed to manage and streamline the process of integrating new employees or clients into the company. This object typically contains fields and records pertinent to the onboarding process, including start dates, completion dates, assigned tasks, responsible personnel, and status updates. It serves as a centralized repository to track the progress and details of each onboarding instance, ensuring that all necessary steps are completed efficiently and consistently. Additionally, the object may include relationships or lookups to other relevant Salesforce objects, such as Contacts, Accounts, or Tasks, to provide a comprehensive view of the onboarding journey.

Name: Credit Conversion
Description: Credit Conversion stores the conversion between a UOM Quantity Dimension (e.g., ‘1K API Calls’) and a Credit.  For example, 1 Credit can be used to consume resource like 1K API Calls, 60 Computing Minutes, 100G Database Storage, etc.

Name: Product Group
Description:
A product group defines a group of product options within a bundle product.  It is also referred to as a feature in a bundle product.

You can add restrictions to product options in a product group, or apply price tags to all product options in a product group.

For example, you may define Product Groups named Platform, Analytics, Devices, etc.  In a bundle, you can group a set of platform-related product options into the Platform group.

Name: Payment Application

Name: Price Tag
Description:
A price tag defines a tiered price structure or tiered discount structure.  A price tag may contain one or more price tiers.  

A price tag can be associated with a bundle product, a product, a product option, a product group, a quote line item, and an order product.  There can be more than one price tag associated with these objects.

At quoting or ordering time, Nue Revenue Engine will automatically apply price tags when applicable.

Name: Price Tier
Description:
A price tier defines the price for a particular quantity range or a subscription term range.  

For example, the price is $10 per unit for 1-10 units; Or a discount of 10% can be applied for 1-100 units, and a discount of $1000 can be applied for over 1000 units.

Name: Product Feature
Description: A product feature defines a feature of the product.  For a bundle product, a product feature defines the relationship between the bundle product and its product groups.

Name: Product Option
Description: A product option defines the optionality of a product within a bundle product.  For example, a product can be a bundled product, or an add-on in a bundle.

Name: UOM
Description:
A Unit of Measure (UOM) is the definable unit that you measure for a product.  For example, User/Year, User/Month. 

A product can have one or more UOMs, and have different list prices for different UOMs.

Name: Sonar Instance
Description: The Custom object "Sonar Instance" represents a unique instance of the Sonar application used by the company. It contains data related to the configuration and usage of the application, including but not limited to user accounts, settings, permissions, and usage metrics. This object is designed to facilitate monitoring and management of the Sonar application and its associated data within the Salesforce platform.
